{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "cab-booking-zalopay-testing",
		"name": "CAB Booking - ZaloPay Payment Testing",
		"description": "Postman collection for testing ZaloPay payment integration in CAB Booking system. This collection covers the full payment flow including charge creation, callback simulation, and payment status queries.\n\n## Prerequisites\n1. Payment Service must be running on port 8090\n2. ZaloPay Sandbox credentials are pre-configured:\n   - App ID: 2553\n   - Key1: PcY4iZIKFCIdgZvA6ueMcMHHUbRLYjPL\n   - Key2: kLtgPl8HHhfvMuDHPwKfgfsY4Ydm9eIz\n\n## Test Flow\n1. **Create Payment** - Initiate a ZaloPay payment charge\n2. **Check Payment Status** - Query payment by booking ID or transaction ID\n3. **Simulate Callback** - Test the callback webhook (for sandbox testing)\n\n## Notes\n- For local testing, use ngrok to expose callback URLs\n- Update ZALOPAY_CALLBACK_URL in .env when using new ngrok URLs",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "baseUrl",
			"value": "http://localhost:8090",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "bookingId",
			"value": "BK-{{$timestamp}}",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "customerId",
			"value": "CUST-001",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "transactionId",
			"value": "txn_{{$timestamp}}",
			"type": "string"
		}
	],
	"auth": {
		"type": "bearer",
		"bearer": [
			{
				"key": "token",
				"value": "test-token",
				"type": "string"
			}
		]
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "1. Create ZaloPay Payment",
			"event": [
				{
					"listen": "test",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"pm.test('Response status is 200', function() {",
							"    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
							"});",
							"",
							"pm.test('Response has success or pending status', function() {",
							"    const response = pm.response.json();",
							"    pm.expect(response.result).to.have.property('status');",
							"    const status = response.result.status;",
							"    pm.expect(['SUCCESS', 'PENDING', 'FAILED']).to.include(status);",
							"});",
							"",
							"pm.test('Response contains payment gateway info', function() {",
							"    const response = pm.response.json();",
							"    pm.expect(response.result).to.have.any.keys(['gatewayTransactionId', 'payUrl', 'zaloPayAppTransId']);",
							"});",
							"",
							"// Store transaction ID for subsequent requests",
							"if (pm.response.json().result && pm.response.json().result.transactionId) {",
							"    pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', pm.response.json().result.transactionId);",
							"}",
							"",
							"// Store booking ID",
							"if (pm.response.json().result && pm.response.json().result.bookingId) {",
							"    pm.collectionVariables.set('bookingId', pm.response.json().result.bookingId);",
							"}",
							"",
							"// Store ZaloPay specific values",
							"const response = pm.response.json();",
							"if (response.result) {",
							"    if (response.result.zaloPayAppTransId) {",
							"        pm.collectionVariables.set('zaloPayAppTransId', response.result.zaloPayAppTransId);",
							"    }",
							"    if (response.result.zaloPayOrderToken) {",
							"        pm.collectionVariables.set('zaloPayOrderToken', response.result.zaloPayOrderToken);",
							"    }",
							"}",
							"",
							"console.log('Transaction created:', pm.response.json());"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {}
					}
				},
				{
					"listen": "prerequest",
					"script": {
						"exec": [
							"// Generate unique values for each request",
							"const now = Date.now();",
							"pm.collectionVariables.set('bookingId', 'BK-' + now);",
							"pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', 'txn_' + now);",
							"",
							"console.log('Generated IDs:', {",
							"    bookingId: pm.collectionVariables.get('bookingId'),",
							"    transactionId: pm.collectionVariables.get('transactionId')",
							"});"
						],
						"type": "text/javascript",
						"packages": {}
					}
				}
			],
			"request": {
				"auth": {
					"type": "bearer",
					"bearer": [
						{
							"key": "token",
							"value": "test-token",
							"type": "string"
						}
					]
				},
				"method": "POST",
				"header": [
					{
						"key": "Content-Type",
						"value": "application/json"
					},
					{
						"key": "X-Idempotency-Key",
						"value": "{{idempotencyKey}}",
						"type": "text"
					}
				],
				"body": {
					"mode": "raw",
					"raw": "{\n    \"bookingId\": \"{{bookingId}}\",\n    \"customerId\": \"{{customerId}}\",\n    \"amount\": 50000,\n    \"paymentMethod\": \"ZALOPAY\",\n    \"currency\": \"VND\",\n    \"description\": \"Test ZaloPay payment for cab booking\"\n}",
					"options": {
						"raw": {
							"language": "json"
						}
					}
				},
				"url": {
					"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/payments/charge",
					"host": [
						"{{baseUrl}}"
					],
					"path": [
						"api",
						"payments",
						"charge"
					]
				},
				"description": "Creates a new ZaloPay payment charge. This endpoint initiates the payment saga and returns a payment URL for the customer to complete payment.\n\n**Response includes:**\n- `payUrl` - URL to redirect customer for payment\n- `zaloPayAppTransId` - ZaloPay transaction ID\n- `zaloPayOrderToken` - Order token for tracking\n\n**Test Scenarios:**\n1. Valid payment request\n2. Duplicate request with same idempotency key\n3. Invalid amount (below 1000 VND)\n4. Missing required fields"
			},
			"response": []
		},
